((SELECT id FROM "legacy".crops WHERE label = 'Ryegrass, Annual' and zone = 5),(SELECT id FROM "legacy".data_keys WHERE key = 'notes:_goals'),'Italian ryegrass is a biennial; needs vernalization to set seed and reliably winter kills in some areas, hence the nickname "annual ryegrass." There are true annual ryegrasses: these are called Westerwolds. They do not have a vernalization requirement to set seed, so management is needed to prevent volunteers. Cultivar matters hugely when using ryegrass as a cover crop because it affects the likelihood of winterkill and how challenging it will be to manage in rotation.'),
